name: Dengue fever
summary: The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) has issued warnings about an increase in dengue fever risk in the United States due to a surge in global cases. The CDC advises travelers to practice usual precautions, including using insect repellent, wearing long sleeves, and avoiding areas with standing water. According to various news sources, the CDC warns healthcare providers to be vigilant for dengue fever, as it has spread to new regions within the US, including a confirmed case of locally transmitted dengue fever in Hillsborough County, Florida. name: Jamaal Bowman
summary: Jamaal Bowman, a member of the progressive "Squad" in the US House of Representatives, has lost his re-election bid to George Latimer, a pro-Israel centrist, in the Democratic primary. The race garnered significant attention due to the record-breaking $14.5 million spent by the American Israel Public Affairs Committee (AIPAC), a pro-Israel lobby, in support of Latimer. Critics have accused AIPAC of "overkill" in its campaign against Bowman, who has been a vocal critic of Israel's treatment of Palestinians. The outcome of the primary has sparked debate about the influence of pro-Israel spending in US politics and the division within the Democratic Party over the issue of Israel and Palestine.
